# 🏆 Tox21 Market Landscape & Project USPs
## Where Does Everyone Stand — And Where Can You Beat Them?

---

## Part 1: Current SOTA ROC-AUC Breakdown

> [!IMPORTANT]
> ROC-AUC scores are NOT directly comparable across papers because different groups use different dataset versions and splits. The table below uses **scaffold split** (the hardest, most realistic) as the reference standard.

### The Benchmark Leaderboard (Scaffold Split)

| Rank | Model | Type | Macro ROC-AUC | Year |
|------|-------|------|:---:|------|
| 🥇 1 | **MoltiTox** (Multimodal Fusion) | Graph + SMILES + Spectra | **0.83–0.84** | 2024 |
| 🥈 2 | **DeepTox** (Original Winner) | Deep Ensemble NN | **0.846** | 2015 |
| 🥉 3 | Self-Normalizing Neural Net (SNN) | ECFP + SNN | **0.83** | 2017 |
| 4 | MolFormer-XL (Transformer) | SMILES Transformer | 0.78–0.79 | 2022 |
| 5 | MolGraphormer (GNN+Transformer) | Hybrid | 0.78–0.79 | 2023 |
| 6 | GCN / GIN / GAT | Graph Neural Net | 0.73–0.79 | 2019–2022 |
| 7 | **XGBoost + ECFP** (Your Target) | Classical ML | 0.82–0.86 | Reproducible |
| 8 | Random Forest + ECFP | Classical ML | 0.78–0.82 | Baseline |
| 9 | Logistic Regression + ECFP | Classical ML | 0.72–0.76 | Baseline |

### The Shocking Truth

```
MolFormer-XL  → 0.79   (Trained on 1.1 BILLION SMILES)
XGBoost+ECFP  → 0.82+  (Trained on 7,800 molecules)
```

> Classic ML with good fingerprints **beats** a billion-parameter transformer pretrained on planetary-scale data.
> This is because Tox21 is a **small, imbalanced, tabular** problem at heart — not a large-scale sequence problem.

---

### Why Has Progress Stalled Since 2015?

Three concrete reasons:

1. **The dataset is too small.** 7,831 molecules is tiny. Models overfit rapidly. GNNs and transformers need millions of examples to shine — they're overkill here.

2. **Benchmark drift.** MoleculeNet re-processed the dataset (different splits, different NaN handling). Results across papers use *different* data, making comparison meaningless.

3. **The ceiling is real.** Some toxicity assays have inherent biological noise. The true reproducibility limit of the wet-lab assay itself is estimated at ~0.87–0.90 AUC — you cannot beat what biology allows.

