## Part 4: Honest Assessment — What You Should Aim For

### Realistic AUC Targets for Your Project

| Stage | Expected AUC | When |
|-------|:---:|------|
| Logistic Regression baseline | 0.72–0.75 | Week 1 |
| XGBoost + ECFP optimized | 0.82–0.85 | Week 2 |
| XGBoost + ECFP + descriptors | 0.84–0.86 | Week 2 |
| Ensemble (RF + XGB + LGB) | 0.85–0.87 | Week 3 |
| **Goal — beat published DeepTox** | **> 0.846** | Week 3+ |

### The Honest Story

> You probably won't achieve SOTA on raw AUC — multimodal GNNs trained on billion-molecule datasets have a real advantage. But **raw AUC is not your battle.**

Your battle is:
- ✅ **Explainability** — no SOTA model ships with atom-level SHAP maps to the public
- ✅ **Accessibility** — your Streamlit app is free; commercial tools cost $50K/year
- ✅ **Reproducibility** — your pipeline is open, auditable, and scaffold-split validated
- ✅ **Uncertainty** — conformal prediction is novel for this task
- ✅ **Chemist UX** — structural alerts + similarity search + ML + SHAP in one click

